<?xml version="1.0" encoding="ASCII"?>
<caldef:CalDefinitionFile xmlns:caldef="http://www.caltools.gm.com/caldef" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" Description="This caldef file defines the FM specific tuner calibrations.  These calibrations are primarily defined to configure the tuner for specific regions.">
  <CalDefFileVersion>19</CalDefFileVersion>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <Date>27Jun2014</Date>
    <Description>&#xD;
Changes to GIS653_AMFMTunerCombined.caldef  Version 3  27Jun2014&#xD;&#xD;
1.  Delete FMQualityAverageFactor, FMQualityHysteresis, FM_NonRDSLevel, FM_RDSInformationRegion, and FM_Separation as these were NGI based calibrations.  They have been replaced with Harman specific calibrations that perform similar functionality.&#xD;&#xD;
&#xD;
2.  Added the following new cals to support supplier specific calibrations for FMTuner:&#xD;
DirectTuneAllEnabled, FM_BandLowerLimit, FM_BandUpperLimit, FM_Demphasis, FM_Offset, &#xD;
FM_StepSizeBig, FM_StepSizeSmall,FMQualHigh_In, FMQualHigh_Out, FmQualLow_In,&#xD;
FMQualLow_Out, QLevelForNonRdsStations, Thr1_FS,Thr1_Qual, and Thr2_FS,Thr2_Qual.&#xD;&#xD;
&#xD;
3.  Changed description for FM_MemoryScanLevel to indicate this cal is for non-North American markets only.&#xD;&#xD;
&#xD;
      Changes to GIS653_AMFMTunerCombined.caldef  Version 2  08May2014&#xD;&#xD;
&#xD;&#xD;
1. Changed cal names to follow CamelCase format&#xD;&#xD;
2. Deleted the following cals as they are not relevant for Info 3:&#xD;&#xD;
CAL_FASTMANUALTUNESPEED  Defined in tunerHMI.caldef&#xD;&#xD;
CAL_FASTSEEKSPEED  Defined in tunerHMI.caldef&#xD;&#xD;
CAL_SEEKSTOPBIII  DAB cal.  Will be defined in DABTuner.caldef for My18 release&#xD;&#xD;
CAL_SEEKSTOPLBAND  DAB cal.  Will be defined in DABTuner.caldef for My18 release&#xD;&#xD;
CAL_SEEKTIMEOUT  DAB cal.  Will be defined in DABTuner.caldef for My18 release&#xD;&#xD;
SDARS_CHANNEL_LIST_DETAILS_UPDATE_RATE.  Defined as a combined with AM/FM cal in tunerHMI.caldef&#xD;&#xD;
ENABLE_AM_AUDIOMOREFEATURE_TRAFFICINFORMATION_JAPAN   Defined in tunerHMI.caldef&#xD;&#xD;
ENABLE_AM_FM_DAB_AUDIOMOREFEATURE_UPDATESTATIONLIST  Will be defined in DABTuner.caldef for My18 release&#xD;&#xD;
ENABLE_APPLICATION_AUDIO, ENABLE_APPLICATION_DMB, ENABLE_APPLICATIONTRAY_AUDIO, ENABLE_APPLICATIONTRAY_DMB, TA_OFFSET, STRONG_STN_NUM These cals are from NGI and do not apply in this form to Info 3.&#xD;&#xD;
STATION_LIST_UPDATE_RATE and STRONG_STATION_LIST_UPDATE_RATE.  These cals are combined for Info 3.  Combined cal is in tunerHMI.caldef.&#xD;&#xD;
TUNER_PARAMETER_ADJUST_ENABLE has been deleted.  This was a Supplier specific cal from NGI.  &#xD;&#xD;
SCAN_PTIME   Scans are no longer provided. Only Seek and Tune are defined tuning operations.'&#xD;&#xD;
Reviewed with Harman on May 6, 2014.  Also then deleted RefreshStationListMaxValue and RefreshStrongStationListMaxValue.  Moved SensBest to FMTuner.caldef  Added AM_FM_FastSeekRate and AM_FM_FastTuneRate as the tuner needs to process this rate info for press and hold operations. </Description>
    <Author>Alan Budyta</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>4</Version>
    <Date>18Aug2014</Date>
    <Description>This change package addresses additional refinements to tuner cals.  In particular, additional cals have been added that were originally defined in the tunerHMI caldef file.  These cals were deemed to fit better in this caldef file based on GM/Harman reviews.</Description>
    <Author>Alan Budyta</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>5</Version>
    <Date>29SEP14</Date>
    <Description>Add Usage on all components</Description>
    <Author>Scott Rush</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>6</Version>
    <Date>December 1 2014</Date>
    <Description>Release File Change Log:  Cal Def File Version 6.  December 2, 2014
Here is a summary of the changes for this release based on reviews with Harman:

1.  Deleted FM_BandUpperLimit and FM_BandLowerLimit.  Instead the cal ranges will be defined with the existing cal called the FM_Range enumeration.  This will add consistency with the AM Band.  

2.  MaxPIWaitTime.  Changed max value from 250 to 3500 to accommodate default value setting.

3.  FM_StepSizeSmall.  Deleted this cal as it is not required for Info 3 programs.

4.  FM_StepSizeBig.  Changed name to FM_StepSize as only 1 step size will be used for Info 3 programs.

5. FM_HighCut.  Added this calibration as an enumeration to provide a regional selection for the high cut filter parameter settings defined in GMW16273.  Renamed original FM_HighCut to FM_HighCutRollOff as this is an integer value that will provide customization for rolloff.

6. FM_TimeToProductAudio. Added this calibration to define the time in msec to delay producing audio after a preset selection, seek/tune, or direct tune process before audio is played to allow for system dynamic switching conditions to dissipate.  See GMW16273.

7.  FM_Separation.  This calibration defines the FM Separation value that can be selected based on the settings defined in GMW16273.

8.  FMLimiting.  Changes this cal type from integer to enumeration to match GMW16273 definition.

9. FM_Autostore.  Deleted this calibration as it is not applicable for Info 3 programs.

10. FM_AutoStoreNonRDSLevel.  Deleted this calibration as it is not applicable for Info 3 programs.

11. FM_AutoStoreRDSAccLevel.  Deleted this calibration as it is not applicable for Info 3 programs.

</Description>
    <Author>Alan Budyta</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>7</Version>
    <Date>06 Feb 2015</Date>
    <Description>The following changes have been made to GIS-653FMTuner.caldef in the release of this file to correct and clarify miscellaneous issues:

1.  Added an RDSActive calibration to enable/disable RDS processing in the tuner.

2.  Added the following calibrations to address the Assembla ticket for tuner reception performance calibrations exposed to the caldef files by Harman.  Also added SS prefix to explicity designate these cals as Harman specific.  This SS prefix should be combined with the Usage field (High/Mid) to sort on these values from any cal database.

SS_FM_StereoLimiter
SS_FM_StereoSensitivitySMS
SS_FM_StereoSensitivitySNS
SS_FM_StereoSlop
SS_FM_StereoStart
SS_FM_SoftMuteLimiter
SS_FM_SoftMuteSensitivityMMS
SS_FM_SoftMuteSensitivityMNS
SS_FM_SoftMuteSlope
SS_FM_SoftMuteStart
SS_FM_HighCutMaxLimit
SS_FM_HighCutSensitivityHMS
SS_FM_HighCutSensitivityHNS
SS_FM_HighCutSlope
SS_FM_HighCutStart

3. Deleted the FM_FrequencyStepSize cal as this is redundant with the FM_StepSize cal which correctly calls out the enumerated ranges.  In addtion, this change makes the naming consistent with the AM caldef file (AM_StepSize).  This issue was defined in Assembla Ticket #1510. </Description>
    <Author>Alan Budyta</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>8</Version>
    <Date>4/17/2015</Date>
    <Description>Per request from Sanghyun Ryu updated Thr2_Qual, Thr1_Qual, Thr2_FS, and Thr1_FS cals in this caldef file to remove usage of Low Radio.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>9</Version>
    <Date>26.05.20215</Date>
    <Description>Deleted TrafficProgramActive,  deleted RegionSwitchingActive (see new FM_RDS_ parameters),  deleted DisplayFMCategories (now at HMI side), TrafficInformationActive (now HMI side),  deleted FM_StepSize (see newFM_RDS_parameters) as an enumeration type CAL, and released the FM_Step_size CAL in place of this CAL as integer type CAL as we are only using one step size for the FM band, deleted RDSActive (see new FM_RDS_ parameters),  deleted FM_Range (see new FM_RDS_ parameters), deleted PICodeConfiguration (not used), added FM_Start_Frequency, FM_Stop_Frequency, FM_step_size_small, FM_step_size_big, FM_RDS_AF_switching_enabled, FM_RDS_TP_enabled, FM_RDS_TA_enabled, FM_RDS_EON_enabled, FM_RDS_TMC_enabled, FM_RDS_PI_ignore, FM_RDS_REG_switching_enabled, FM_RDS_PTY31_enabled, and FM_RDS_Clocktime_enabled.</Description>
    <Author>Christian Gro&#xdf;</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>10</Version>
    <Date>19.06.2015</Date>
    <Description>Removed FM_Step_size_small,  FM_Step_size_big and added FM_Step_size as we are only using one step size for the FM band.</Description>
    <Author>Christian Gro&#xdf;</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>11</Version>
    <Date>6NOV2015</Date>
    <Description>The RDS_Configuration calibration was added into this release to provide more granular control of RDS features for given vehicle markets.</Description>
    <Author>Alan Budyta</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>12</Version>
    <Date>3/17/2016</Date>
    <Description>Wtihin this caldef file, made the following updates: Per request from Alan Budyta removed usage of CSM High and Mid for the following four CALs that were confirmed only to be needed for the Low Radio: 1.) AF_Quality, 2.) FM_RDS_EON_enabled, 3.) RegionalQualityControl, and 4.) FM_HighCutRollOff. Also, per request from Alan Budyta updated the max value from 15 to 130 for the AF_LastLeadCount CAL.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>13</Version>
    <Date>2016-Jun-28</Date>
    <Description>Clean up of cals as per CR# 1096165. 1. Deleted SS_REG_AF_Switching_Speed integer caldef.2. Added enum SS_REG_AF_Switching_Speed. 3. Added missing cal FMSingleTunerEnable.4. Deleted RDS_Configuration, 5. Deleted FM_RDS_TA_enabled, 6. Added FM_RDS_PSN_RT_Enabled, 7. Added FM_RDS_PTY_enabled, revised MaxPIWaitTime type from float to integer and range, unit, default value.  8. Revised default values to meet CG2510 for the following cals per Harman (RF Principle Engr.Nasserullah Khan) request dated 2016-Jun-16. FMQualLow_In  change from 70 to 82,FMQualLow_Out change from 40 to 43, SS_FM_HighCutStart change from 0 to 5.</Description>
    <Author>Kiran Soni</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>14</Version>
    <Date>2016-Dec-08 </Date>
    <Description>Revising the description for the FM_Demphasis calibration for clarification.</Description>
    <Author>Kiran Soni</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>15</Version>
    <Date>6/15/2017</Date>
    <Description>Updated the usage field for all of the calibration to support the new &quot;Global A/B&quot; categorization in the CalDef tool.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>16</Version>
    <Date>10/2/2017</Date>
    <Description>Within the GIS653_FMTuner.caldef file, added GEM usage to all of the calibrations within this caldef, except for the following eighteen calibrations within this caldef file: 1.) SS_BWLEV_Automatic_bandwidth_control_sensitivity_at_low_level, 2.) SS_BWS_Automatic_bandwidth_control_sensitivity,  3.) SS_FM_HighCutMaxLimit, 4.) SS_FM_HighCutSensitivityHMS, 5.) SS_FM_HighCutSensitivityHNS, 6.) SS_FM_HighCutSlope, 7.) SS_FM_HighCutStart, 8.) SS_FM_SoftMuteLimiter,  9.) SS_FM_SoftMuteSensitivityMMS, 10.) SS_FM_SoftMuteSensitivityMNS, 11.) SS_FM_SoftMuteSlope, 12.) SS_FM_SoftMuteStart, 13.) SS_FM_StereoLimiter, 14.) SS_FM_StereoSensitivitySMS, 15.) SS_FM_StereoSensitivitySNS, 16.) SS_FM_StereoSlope, 17.) SS_FM_StereoStart, and 18.) SS_REG_AF_Switching_Speed.  Note, did not add GEM usage for these  eighteen calibrations since these eigheen calibraions did not fall within the current criteria of requiring GEM usage, which are any calibrations that would be used for Low Radio Global B application.</Description>
    <Author>Ginnard Kimbrough</Author>
  </CalDefFileChangeRecord>
  <CalDefFileChangeRecord>
    <Version>17</Version>
    <Date>05/10/2018</Date>
    <Description>GMW16273 related changes. CR#1768009. 1. Deleted FM_Limiting, FM_SoftMuteThreshold - previous tables modified or no longer exists in updated version of GMW</Description>
