  <CalDefinition Description="The DirectTuneAllEnabled calibration when TRUE, allows the tuner to receive and process (i.e., tune to) any frequency, regardless of the internal tuner frequency step size. If this calibration is set to FALSE, the tuner shall only process Direct Tune entries that align with the internal tuner frequency step size.  The provides the capability to tune to any theoretical frequency within a given frequency range when a market requires this support.  The default state for this calibration is FALSE." Name="DirectTuneAllEnabled" References="GIS-653-2315 AM/FM Direct Tune Function" Usage="LOW,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU">
    <CalID>_ULdIcM_GEeObGfP4S25hHw</CalID>
    <Type>Boolean</Type>
    <Version>3</Version>
    <CalDefChangeRecord>
      <Version>1</Version>
      <Date>26.05.2015</Date>
