  <CalDefinition Description="This boolean parameter defines whether the program type 31 alarm is used. RDS defines a coding of up to 31 pre-defined programme types (e.g., in Europe: PTY1 News, PTY6 Drama, PTY11 Rock music) allows users to find similar programming by genre. PTY31 seems to be reserved for emergency announcements in the event of natural disasters or other major calamities. Semantics: true: PTY31 alarm announcement active" Name="FM_RDS_PTY31_enabled" References="GIS-338-102D PTY 31" Usage="LOW,MID,HIGH,GEM,GLOBALA,GLOBALB,ENTRY_VCU,VCU">
